<br>
I don't know what, exactly, happened, but I do know that one or more people went into that battle without knowledge of their enemy, and failed to listen to those that had the knowledge.<br>
<br>
So I ask ye.. what now? Are you allowed to continue holding the Ragefire camp for another week, or are you required to defer to the next in line?<br>
<br>
Let me know. If I'm online, I'll lend my assistance, and that of anyone else I can provoke to battle.<br>
<br>
<br>
~Kaycerzan Deusabsconditus, Knight of Valor<br>
~~Sanctus Covenir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/utaku645.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taku645</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/25/02 12:40:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kosak..</span><hr size=1> Kosak still holds the rage camp.  Be prepared for a good ol' fashioned Dragon beatdown in the very near future.  Also of note that Dopy is next in line. <p><br><br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=88585" target="calendar">&#358;å&#312;&#363;</a><br>
55 Cleric<br>
LoLF Officer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uyarrick40k.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yarrick40k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/25/02 3:44:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kosak..</span><hr size=1> So, for those of us that weren't there, what all happened?  Rage pop + get kill stolen yet again?<br>
<br>
-Yarrick<br>
Guild Leader of Mystic Defiance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/udarvanirongutt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darvan Irongutt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/25/02 3:58:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kosak..</span><hr size=1> Heres the short and skinny of what out happened.<br>
<br>
Part 1: Rage popped, 60+ people showed up to killl, before everyone was buffed/grouped someone ran in front of rage which agroed him. That person then brought rage to the group after being asked many, many times to die on the field. The person asked, before he died, if he could get a rez..../sigh So the person did eventually die.<br>
<br>
Part 2: The aforementioned agro caused rage to come charging back at the group, thus people started attacking. An enchanter tried many, many times to mez the merchant so a big bad dragon wouldnt spawn on ungrouped, unbuffed people. I can see why this happened though. I bet that was some major battle spam<br>
<br>
Part 3: After a complete wipe out, we all regrouped. By that time, Rage had wandered off in the zone and eventually depopped. <br>
<br>
I banged my knuckles on my desk until they bled to vent personal anger. Darvan dueled Blolyp to vent some of his anger. Then I went to bed.<br>
<br>
Thats pretty much what happened. If I left something out, let me know <p><br><br><p><center>
<img src="http://www.katznstuff.com/lolf/darvan.jpg">
</center><br>
<center><b><font color=red>In Excelsis Precedo Bellator Decerte Adversa Incurro Invadoria<br><p>Excellence In the highest The Warrior Will fight to the finish Against all opposition
Attack! Invade!</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uyarrick40k.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yarrick40k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/25/02 5:34:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kosak..</span><hr size=1> Ugg, major suckage.  If only you could mes your own tanks...<br>
<br>
Sorry to hear it went bad.  At least Kosak still has the camp.. *shrug*<br>
<br>
Hopefully I'll be around next time he pops.  Would love to still help you guys out (all of Mystic Defiance too).<br>
<br>
-Yarrick<br>
Guild Leader of Mystic Defiance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uravilicuslolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravilicus LoLF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/25/02 8:24:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kosak..</span><hr size=1> You offer is much appreciated but I believe it has been agreed that only those people specifically invited to help should come to help.  In all honesty we have overkill when it comes to this kill and when too many are involved it is easier to lose focus and organization, which ultimately becomes the more difficult obstacle to overcome than the mob itself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/umelaniecharissesongweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Melanie Charisse Songweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/25/02 10:32:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://leyna.netfirms.com/UsAndSummonElse.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kosak..</span><hr size=1> What Darvan said is exactly what happened except in between the 1. and 2. there's an addition. When the person agroed Rage merchant and ask if he could get a rez if he die away from us and eventually died.<br>
<br>
However a monk went and pull/agro it to the gathering people which then proceed to a complete wipe out. Kosak is currently sat there camping the camp again.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately we may have problem as an FU person is camping there(well he will do it full time next week,which may then be Dopy's turn) with his druid at least and occasionaly his cleric(?). As well as few other guilds seem to be in the zone all the time now including Blades of Law. For those of you who don't know BoL guild have all of a sudden changed to FFA(confirmed by a friend who was annoyed at the sudden change as well). Also I think the fact that Rage depop musta spread round to almost EVERY guild on the server which makes them think that we will never be able to do the camp and can't gather enough troops in time compared to them. *shrug* <p><CENTER><img src="http://leyna.netfirms.com/BaronessTriellSig.jpg"></CENTER> 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ucloudsoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cloudsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/26/02 1:29:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kosak..</span><hr size=1> <br>
Popped late in the night 3:00am est, 8:00am my time I think so that didn't help, and we had 40+ people there over half of whom I'd never seen in my life before.<br>
<br>
Next time, need an assigned raid leader who knows the mob available with kosak at all times or at least on to issue orders and need to filter out the people we don't need and who may not follow orders as well as the regulars.<br>
<br>
I arrived just as rage had been pulled, ikipu shouted 5 or 6 times to call people off and they just ignored him, he then tried chain mezzing but the dragon poped.<br>
<br>
It was liked lemmings to the slaughter, most stupid incident I've seen in a long time, Rage started his own aoe group and mowed down 30+ people most of em LFG and unbuffed in the space of a couple of mins.<br>
<br>
<br>
Baron Eldark<br>
<br>
Dark Legion<br>
